content:
Paid $9.50 for chicken Bryani and the size of the breast meat was half the size of what it was. It was ridiculous and totally unacceptable to be given a miserable chicken fillet looking portion! We have been their regular so we knew the portion very well and we’d alway ask for breast meat in which he argued it was thigh.  While we can understand inflation has shrunk the chicken portion but the Chinese man cashier was so lamely defensive that to say that all their chicken breast meat were the same size, all along looking like fillet size. Hey, anyone who has a decent eyesight could tell the difference between a chicken quarter white (breast meat with wing attached) vs a slab of chicken fillet. He was so rude to outrightly challenged me to validate his claim. I asked the Indian lady server to pick another piece of a decent to prove him wrong that there were bigger piece! Pl don’t take advantage of consumer by being such a bully.  They should weigh the portion instead of offending customer.
I was to upset to take the photo before they unwilling changed to the bigger piece I chose. They also  threw the smaller fillet looking piece right before my eye!

@North point foodcourt
